findings.fix_suggestion:
Create an eslint.config.js file at the project root. Example:
```js
import js from '@eslint/js';

export default [
  js.configs.recommended,
  {
    files: ['lambda/**/*.mjs'],
    languageOptions: {
      ecmaVersion: 'latest',
      sourceType: 'module',
      globals: { console: 'readonly' }
    },
    rules: {
      'no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_' }]
    }
  }
];
```

Create a vitest.config.js at the project root to exclude the terraform directory:
```js
import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';
export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    globals: true,
    environment: 'node',
    exclude: ['node_modules/**', 'terraform/**']
  }
});
```

Add optional password strength check. Recommend but don't require: at least 1 uppercase, 1 lowercase, 1 number, 1 symbol. Example: 
```js
const hasComplexity = /[A-Z]/.test(password) && /[a-z]/.test(password) && /[0-9]/.test(password);
if (!hasComplexity) return res(400, { error: 'Password should include uppercase, lowercase, and numbers', hint: 'This is a recommendation; your password is accepted.' }, origin);
```
Or return it as a warning in response: { ok: true, passwordStrength: 'weak' }.
